Section 1:
1 L.D. 288
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 TAXATION
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 188, L.D. 288, “An Act to Make
10 Technical Changes to Maine's Tax Laws”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of Part B.
12 Amend the bill in Part C by striking out all of section 13.
13 Amend the bill by striking out all of Part D.
14 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
15 number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This amendment removes Part B from the bill, which contains changes that:
18 1. Clarify that the retail sale exclusion for the sale or lease or rental of tangible personal
19 property for further lease or rental does not include the further casual sale or rental of the
20 tangible personal property;
21 2. Remove references to sale and leaseback transactions from the sales tax exemption
22 for machinery and equipment; and
23 3. Clarify the timing of the testing period for the sales tax exemption for leases for
24 certain instrumentalities of interstate or foreign commerce.
25 The amendment also removes Part D, which removes and replaces gendered language
26 in laws governing property taxes and certain other provisions and makes other changes to
27 conform with current drafting standards.
28 The amendment also removes changes to a section of law that was repealed by Public
29 Law 2025, chapter 2, Part RR.
Page 1 - 132LR0154(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
